<doc id="385944" wikidata="Q40007" url="?curid=385944" title="Pontryagin class">
<text>In mathematics, the Pontryagin classes, named after Lev Pontryagin, are certain characteristic classes of real vector bundles. The Pontryagin classes lie in cohomology groups with degrees a multiple of four.

== Definition ==
Given a real vector bundle formula_1 over formula_2, its formula_3-th Pontryagin class formula_4 is defined as 
:formula_5
where:
*formula_6 denotes the formula_7-th Chern class of the complexification formula_8 of formula_1, 
*formula_10 is the formula_11-cohomology group of formula_2 with integer coefficients.

The rational Pontryagin class formula_13 is defined to be the image of formula_4 in formula_15, the formula_11-cohomology group of formula_2 with rational coefficients.

== Properties ==
The total Pontryagin class 
:formula_18
is (modulo 2-torsion) multiplicative with respect to 
Whitney sum of vector bundles, i.e., 
