and so on.

The vanishing of the Pontryagin classes and Stiefel–Whitney classes of a vector bundle does not guarantee that the vector bundle is trivial. For example, up to vector bundle isomorphism, there is a unique nontrivial rank 10 vector bundle formula_26 over the 9-sphere. (The clutching function for formula_26 arises from the homotopy group formula_28.) The Pontryagin classes and Stiefel-Whitney classes all vanish: the Pontryagin classes don&#x27;t exist in degree 9, and the Stiefel–Whitney class formula_29 of formula_26 vanishes by the Wu formula formula_31. Moreover, this vector bundle is stably nontrivial, i.e. the Whitney sum of formula_26 with any trivial bundle remains nontrivial. 

Given a formula_33-dimensional vector bundle formula_1 we have 
